com.javadude.annotation
Annotation Type Bean

@Retention(value=SOURCE)
@Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface Bean

An annotation that requests to generate Bean code for the annotated class.

This annotation marks a class as a JavaBean and allows generation of code based on the specified attributes.

If you annotate a class with @Bean, the annotation processor will generate a superclass containing the requested generated code. The name of the generated class is the same as the annotated class with a suffix of "Gen". To use this annotation, you must define your class to extend the generated superclass. For example:

@Bean(...)
 public class Foo extends FooGen { ...}

If you need to extend another class, you can ask the Bean annotation processor to add an extends clause to the generated class using the "superclass" attribute. For example, if you wanted class Foo to extend class Fee, you would write:

@Bean(superclass="Fee", ...)
 public class Foo extends FooGen { ...}

The generated superclass would look like

public class FooGen extends Fee {...}

If the required superclass is not in the same package as the annotated class, you need to fully qualify it:

@Bean(superclass="x.y.Fee",...)

Optional Element Summary
 boolean cloneable
          If true, the generated superclass will implement Cloneable and appropriately override the clone() method.
 boolean createPropertyMap
          If true, generate a createPropertyMap() method in the superclass.
 boolean defineSimpleEqualsAndHashCode
          If true, the generated superclass will include a simple equals() and hashCode() method.
 Delegate[] delegates
          A list of Delegate annotations that specify creation of delegate methods in the generated superclass.
 boolean equalsShouldCheckSuperEquals
          If true, the generated superclass' equals() method will first check super.equals(), and return false if its result is false.
 NullObject[] nullObjectImplementations
          A list of NullObject annotations that specify creation of null stub methods in the generated superclass.
 Observer[] observers
          A list of Observer annotations that specify observer pattern creation in the generated superclass.
 boolean overrideParamString
          If true, the superclass will add Override to the generated paramString method and include the contents of its superclass' paramString() method.
 Property[] properties
          A list of Property annotations that define properties to be generated in the generated superclass.
 Access reader
          Specifies the default access level of the setter methods generated for any defined properties
 java.lang.Class<?> superclass
          Defines the class you would like to extend.
 java.lang.String superclassString
          Defines the class you would like to extend.
 java.lang.String superConstructorArgs
          Parameter definition for the constructor in the generated superclass.
 java.lang.String superConstructorSuperCall
          Arguments to the super(...) call that will be generated in the superclass' constructor.
 Access writer
          Specifies the default access level of the getter methods generated for any defined properties
 

superclass

public abstract java.lang.Class<?> superclass
Defines the class you would like to extend. Only one of superclass or superclassString maybe specified

Default:
java.lang.Void.class

superclassString

public abstract java.lang.String superclassString
Defines the class you would like to extend. If this superclass is in the same package as the annotated class, you only need to specify its name. If the superclass is in a different package, you must fully-qualify it. Only one of superclass or superclassString maybe specified

Default:
""

superConstructorArgs

public abstract java.lang.String superConstructorArgs
Parameter definition for the constructor in the generated superclass.

Default:
""

superConstructorSuperCall

public abstract java.lang.String superConstructorSuperCall
Arguments to the super(...) call that will be generated in the superclass' constructor. Usually used with superConstructorArgs.

Default:
""

cloneable

public abstract boolean cloneable
If true, the generated superclass will implement Cloneable and appropriately override the clone() method.

Default:
false

overrideParamString

public abstract boolean overrideParamString
If true, the superclass will add Override to the generated paramString method and include the contents of its superclass' paramString() method.

Default:
false

defineSimpleEqualsAndHashCode

public abstract boolean defineSimpleEqualsAndHashCode
If true, the generated superclass will include a simple equals() and hashCode() method.

Default:
false

equalsShouldCheckSuperEquals

public abstract boolean equalsShouldCheckSuperEquals
If true, the generated superclass' equals() method will first check super.equals(), and return false if its result is false.

Default:
false

createPropertyMap

public abstract boolean createPropertyMap
If true, generate a createPropertyMap() method in the superclass. This method will generate a Map that contains property name/values for properties defined via an Property annotation inside this bean.

Default:
false

properties

public abstract Property[] properties
A list of Property annotations that define properties to be generated in the generated superclass.

Default:
{}

observers

public abstract Observer[] observers
A list of Observer annotations that specify observer pattern creation in the generated superclass.

Default:
{}

delegates

public abstract Delegate[] delegates
A list of Delegate annotations that specify creation of delegate methods in the generated superclass.

Default:
{}

nullObjectImplementations

public abstract NullObject[] nullObjectImplementations
A list of NullObject annotations that specify creation of null stub methods in the generated superclass.

Default:
{}

reader

public abstract Access reader
Specifies the default access level of the setter methods generated for any defined properties

Default:
com.javadude.annotation.Access.PUBLIC

writer

public abstract Access writer
Specifies the default access level of the getter methods generated for any defined properties

Default:
com.javadude.annotation.Access.PUBLIC
